<subSubSection type="discussion">
<paragraph pageNumber="1">
Bagrid catfishes of the genus 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:AA1B525C-6B62-477E-A45B-87C44FE5987A" class="Actinopterygii" family="Bagridae" genus="Rita" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Rita Bleeker 1854:122" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="1" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Rita Bleeker, 1854</taxonomicName>
are found in large rivers throughout the Indian subcontinent and Myanmar, and are capable of reaching sizes to 1500 mm TL (Talwar and Jhingran, 1991), although mature specimens of ca. 200-300 mm SL are more commonly encountered. The genus is diagnosed by the following synapomorphies (Mo, 1991): single pair of mandibular barbels, elongated Weberian apparatus firmly sutured to the basioccipital, and the sensory canal on the posttemporal enclosed within the bone. 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:AA1B525C-6B62-477E-A45B-87C44FE5987A" class="Actinopterygii" family="Bagridae" genus="Rita" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Rita Bleeker 1854:122" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="1" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Rita</taxonomicName>
and its sister taxon 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:52BAA8FE-77DF-489C-9E3C-0C748E301356" class="Actinopterygii" family="Bagridae" genus="Nanobagrus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Nanobagrus Mo 1991:(125), 143" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="1" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Nanobagrus Mo, 1991</taxonomicName>
are the sister group to all other members of Bagridae (Mo, 1991). The most recent review of 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:AA1B525C-6B62-477E-A45B-87C44FE5987A" class="Actinopterygii" family="Bagridae" genus="Rita" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Rita Bleeker 1854:122" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="1" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Rita</taxonomicName>
was provided by Ferraris (1999) in his redescription of 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:580E940E-8827-4A0D-88C0-B27303D17F51" class="Actinopterygii" family="Bagridae" genus="Rita" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Rita sacerdotum Anderson 1879:864" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="1" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="sacerdotum">R. sacerdotum Anderson, 1879</taxonomicName>
in which five valid species of 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:AA1B525C-6B62-477E-A45B-87C44FE5987A" class="Actinopterygii" family="Bagridae" genus="Rita" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Rita Bleeker 1854:122" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="1" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Rita</taxonomicName>
were recognized: 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:C0E75F40-1F93-4303-9A83-CD207BDB66A2" class="Actinopterygii" family="Bagridae" genus="Rita" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Pimelodus rita Hamilton 1822:165, 376" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="1" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="rita">R. rita(Hamilton, 1822)</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName class="Actinopterygii" family="Bagridae" genus="Rita" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="1" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="gogra">R. gogra (Sykes, 1839)</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName class="Actinopterygii" family="Bagridae" genus="Rita" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="1" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="kuturnee">R. kuturnee (Sykes, 1839)</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:6F22EBE1-4F8F-4650-88CD-DD4C99BBDFD8" class="Actinopterygii" family="Bagridae" genus="Rita" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Rita chrysea Day 1877:455" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="1" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="chrysea">R. chrysea Day, 1877</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:580E940E-8827-4A0D-88C0-B27303D17F51" class="Actinopterygii" family="Bagridae" genus="Rita" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Rita sacerdotum Anderson 1879:864" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="1" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="sacerdotum">R. sacerdotum Anderson, 1879</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageNumber="2">
While comparing material identified as 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:C0E75F40-1F93-4303-9A83-CD207BDB66A2" class="Actinopterygii" family="Bagridae" genus="Rita" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Pimelodus rita Hamilton 1822:165, 376" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="2" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="rita">Rita rita</taxonomicName>
from the Ganges and the Indus River drainages, differences were observed which suggested that the Indus River material belong to an undescribed species, which is described below.
</paragraph>
